  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to assess the safety and effect of Viusid (bags of 4 grams)
      administration in the treatment of acute fever of viral etiology as diagnosed by clinical,
      hematologic and serologic parameters. The duration of this open and randomized phase 2
      clinical trial will be 6 days. The estimated number of persons with acute fever of viral
      etiology to be recruited and randomized for the study is 200. The primary outcome measure:
      platelet, leukocyte and granulocyte count will be assessed at the beginning and the end of
      the study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
